article.headline: Rhode Island 83, Saint Louis 67
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Will Daniels led Rhode Island with 19 points and Jimmy Baron chipped in with 17 on 5-of-6 shooting from 3-point range for an 83-67 win over Saint Louis on Wednesday night. Joe Mbang added 12 points in the win and Kahiem Seawright had 11. Tommie Liddell had 23 points for the Billikens. Luke Meyer added 13 points and Kevin Lisch got 10. Rhode Island (16-10, 9-3) took sole possession of first place in the Atlantic 10 standings with its first-ever win over Saint Louis (15-10, 5-6). The Rams closed the first half with an 18-2 run, including 14 unanswered points, to lead 41-23 at the break. They led by as many as 22 points in the second half and were never threatened. Saint Louis pulled within 13 points in the final minute, but never got the deficit into single digits. Darrell Harris, who missed the previous four games for Rhode Island after suffering a high ankle sprain on Jan. 24, chipped in with seven points in seven minutes in the first half.
